I can't find a perfect example of committing to state on arbitrary accounts, but here's an example showing how 2 different smart contracts can be called from one another in the same transaction: https://github.com/o1-labs/o1js/blob/4ca3d1751f4905200d4c6be662ef13276e55f74f/src/examples/zkapps/joint-update.ts#L51

If you just want to assert that a certain token holder has a certain balance, you could do

```ts
// in your smart contract method
const au = AccountUpdate.create(publicKey);
au.account.balance.requireEquals(UInt64.zero);
```
